cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze political manifestos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a hierarchical multi-task structured deep model, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also uses probabilistic soft logic for post-hoc calibration, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with text analysis, which is a subfield of information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with political science, which involves social and political aspects of computing, making cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category.
